<a name="registration">



<h2>Registration</h2>

<h4> Early booking until 5 March </h4>

Student/academic rate £190 <br>
General rate £290 <br>

<h4> Late booking until 24 March </h4>

Student/academic rate £360 <br>
General rate £360 <br>

<p>

Participants need to register through the University of Birmingham online shop.
Payment is by debit or credit card.

<p>

<h2>Accommodation</h2>

We have reserved rooms until the end of February at the <a href="http://www.ibis.com/gb/hotel-5678-ibis-budget-birmingham-centre/index.shtml">Ibis Budget Hotel</a>, which is a short walk from Birmingham New Street station.  

 The price is £225.50 for a single room for 5 nights.  They also have "triple" rooms with bunk beds (double below, single above) for the same price.  Breakfast is an extra £27.50 per person for 5 days.  Please mention "Midlands Graduate School" when you book.


<h2> Travel </h2>

The School of Computer Science is very close to the University (Birmingham) railway station.  There are frequent trains from Birmingham New Street, which in turn has frequent train connections with many cities and with Birmingham Airport.

